sql:
SELECT runs_scored, batting_position
FROM match_performance
WHERE match_id = 1;

SELECT player_id, SUM(runs_scored) AS total_runs_scored
FROM match_performance
GROUP BY player_id;

external_knowledge:
- Top performers refer to the top 5 players with the highest average runs per match.; 
- Cricketers hitting the most runs per match are determined by the average runs per match, calculated as the total runs scored divided by the number of matches played.; 
- A game in cricket is also known as a match.

- Top players are determined based on the highest average runs per innings; 
- The latest performance year for each player is considered; 
- If multiple players have the same average runs per innings, the ones with more matches played are prioritized.
